channel.title: Will Auxy come to Android?
channel.description: I just got a new Google pixel today from and one of the biggest problems I had with switching over from an iPhone was the fact that auxy isn't on the Google play store. I was wondering how many people have had this problem and if maybe there's any way I can get the app back because I absolutely love it and everything about it. I've been using auxy pretty much since it was released and I have so many projects stored on it.

item.title: Will Auxy come to Android?
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
The original batch I read were a few years back. I read an updated article about it a little under a year ago.

Where Auxy (or any app) isn’t dealing with live audio or midi input I don’t know that there is latency, or perceivable latency at least. It’s noticed when you’re recording audio with monitoring, or the “key-press-to-audible-sound” delay with a midi controller attached that it would be a problem.

There is a hardware solution for Samsung phones I think, I never read much about it. Interestingly, Caustic on Android has always worked with a keyboard I think, same with Sunvox, but I don’t know if there are problems with midi input latency.

Read full topic

There are definitely not nearly as many options, unfortunately
